gomodel:SYNGO_2366  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Regulation and synaptic localization of Arcadlin protein\"\nLiteral: \"Arcadlin is naturally expressed in hippocampal neurons and localized at both soma and synapses in association with the marker synaptophysin.\"\n\nThe protein seems postsynaptic based on report of dendritic localization, but I chose the safer term 'synapse (GO:0045202)'.. Experimental description: Dissociated cells: \"Eight-week-old rats were anesthetized and perfused with ...\"" ;
